---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Memory Source Sheet"
  description="A Jewish source sheet exploring themes of memory, forgetting, and selective remembrance"
>
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-900">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
      <header class="mb-12 text-center">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400 mb-2">Memory Source Sheet</h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Matthew Miller</p>
      </header>

      <!-- Theme 1: The Blessing of Forgetting -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mb-6 pb-2 border-b-2 border-cyan-500">The Blessing of Forgetting</h2>
        
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <!-- Sichot HaRan -->
          <section class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400 mb-3">Sichot HaRan, Ch. 26</h3>
            <blockquote class="relative">
              <span class="absolute -top-2 -left-2 text-6xl text-cyan-200 dark:text-cyan-800 font-serif">"</span>
              <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 italic pl-6">Most people think of forgetting as a serious drawback. But to me it has a great advantage. If you did not forget, it would be utterly impossible to serve God. You would remember your entire past, and these memories would drag you down...</p>
            </blockquote>
          </section>

          <!-- David Robson -->
          <section class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400 mb-3">David Robson (BBC)</h3>
            <div class="pl-4 border-l-4 border-cyan-500 dark:border-cyan-400">
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-2">Professor Charan Ranganath:</p>
              <blockquote class="relative">
                <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 italic">"An analogy I like to give is to imagine that I went to your house, and asked: why aren't you a hoarder? ... If we didn't forget anything, we'd be hoarding memories, and you'd never be able to find what you want, when you want it."</p>
              </blockquote>
            </div>
          </section>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Theme 2: Divine Memory and Forgetting -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mb-6 pb-2 border-b-2 border-cyan-500">Divine Memory and Forgetting</h2>
        
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <!-- Job -->
          <section class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400 mb-3">Job 11:6</h3>
            <div class="space-y-3">
              <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 font-hebrew text-xl text-right">וְיַגֶּד־לְךָ֨ ׀ תַּ֥עֲלֻמ֣וֹת חׇכְמָה֮ כִּֽי־כִפְלַ֢יִם לְֽת֫וּשִׁיָּ֥ה וְדַ֡ע כִּֽי־יַשֶּׁ֥ה לְךָ֥ אֱ֝ל֗וֹהַּ מֵעֲוֺנֶֽךָ׃</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 italic">He would tell you the secrets of wisdom... And know that God has overlooked for you some of your iniquity.</p>
              
              <div class="mt-4 space-y-2 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-900 p-4 rounded">
                <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
                  <span class="text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400 font-semibold">Ibn Ezra:</span>
                  <span class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 font-hebrew">ישה - ישכח</span>
                  <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 italic">(forgets)</span>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
                  <span class="text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400 font-semibold">Steinsaltz:</span>
                  <span class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">God can forget your sins, that is, forgive you for them.</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>

          <!-- Rosh Hashanah -->
          <section class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400 mb-3">Rosh Hashanah, Zichronot</h3>
            <div class="space-y-3">
              <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 font-hebrew text-xl text-right">כִּי אֵין שִׁכְחָה לִפְנֵי כִסֵּא כְבוֹדֶֽךָ. וְאֵין נִסְתָּר מִנֶּֽגֶד עֵינֶֽיךָ</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 italic">for there is no forgetfulness before the throne of Your Glory...</p>
            </div>
          </section>

          <!-- Brettler -->
          <section class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400 mb-3">Marc Zvi Brettler</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-2">Zichronot: Asking an Omniscient God to Remember</p>
            <blockquote class="pl-4 border-l-4 border-cyan-500 dark:border-cyan-400">
              <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 italic">"We are asking God to use selective memory, a feature that is well-documented in scientific literature, where it is sometimes called 'selective forgetting.'"</p>
            </blockquote>
          </section>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Theme 3: Memory and Mourning -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mb-6 pb-2 border-b-2 border-cyan-500">Memory and Mourning</h2>
        
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <!-- Rashi -->
          <section class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400 mb-3">Rashi on Genesis 37:35</h3>
            <div class="space-y-3">
              <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 font-hebrew text-xl text-right">וימאן להתנחם. אֵין אָדָם מְקַבֵּל תַּנְחוּמִין עַל הַחַי וְסָבוּר שֶׁמֵּת, שֶׁעַל הַמֵּת נִגְזְרָה גְזֵרָה שֶׁיִּשְׁתַּכַּח מִן הַלֵּב וְלֹא עַל הַחַי</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">A person does not accept consolation for one living whom he believes to be dead, for with regard to the dead it is decreed that he be forgotten from the heart and not with regard to the living.</p>
            </div>
          </section>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Theme 4: Selective Memory -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mb-6 pb-2 border-b-2 border-cyan-500">Selective Memory</h2>
        
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <!-- Yosef -->
          <section class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400 mb-3">Genesis 41:51 - The Naming of Menashe</h3>
            <div class="space-y-3">
              <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 font-hebrew text-xl text-right">וַיִּקְרָ֥א יוֹסֵ֛ף אֶת־שֵׁ֥ם הַבְּכ֖וֹר מְנַשֶּׁ֑ה כִּֽי־נַשַּׁ֤נִי אֱ׳ אֶת־כָּל־עֲמָלִ֔י וְאֵ֖ת כָּל־בֵּ֥ית אָבִֽי׃</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 italic">Joseph named the first-born Manasseh, meaning, "God has made me forget completely my hardship and my parental home."</p>
              
              <div class="mt-4 bg-cyan-50 dark:bg-cyan-900/20 p-4 rounded">
                <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 font-semibold mb-2">Q: How could Yosef have forgotten his parental home?</p>
                <div class="pl-4 border-l-4 border-cyan-500 dark:border-cyan-400">
                  <p class="text-sm text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400 font-semibold">R. Yisrael Salanter:</p>
                  <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Yosef could never have forgotten. Even by naming his son this very name makes him remember. This is a classic case of selective memory.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Theme 5: Technology and Memory -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mb-6 pb-2 border-b-2 border-cyan-500">Technology and Memory</h2>
        
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <!-- Hard Fork -->
          <section class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400 mb-3">Hard Fork Podcast</h3>
            <blockquote class="relative">
              <span class="absolute -top-2 -left-2 text-6xl text-cyan-200 dark:text-cyan-800 font-serif">"</span>
              <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 italic pl-6">What I do worry about, though, is, I actually think it's a good thing that we can forget some things... I found a floppy disk that contained logs of a lot of my old instant message transcripts from middle school.</p>
            </blockquote>
          </section>

          <!-- Gordon Bell -->
          <section class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400 mb-3">James Poulos, The Technology of Memory</h3>
            <div class="pl-4 border-l-4 border-cyan-500 dark:border-cyan-400">
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-2">Gordon Bell:</p>
              <blockquote>
                <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 italic">"I feel much freer about remembering something now. I've got this machine, this slave, that does it."</p>
              </blockquote>
            </div>
          </section>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Theme 6: Literary and Educational Perspectives -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mb-6 pb-2 border-b-2 border-cyan-500">Literary and Educational Perspectives</h2>
        
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <!-- Alexander Pope -->
          <section class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400 mb-3">Alexander Pope, Eloisa to Abelard</h3>
            <blockquote class="text-center">
              <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 italic">
                How happy is the blameless vestal's lot!<br/>
                The world forgetting, by the world forgot<br/>
                Eternal sunshine of the spotless mind!<br/>
                Each pray'r accepted, and each wish resign'd.
              </p>
            </blockquote>
          </section>

          <!-- B.F. Skinner -->
          <section class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400 mb-3">B.F. Skinner</h3>
            <blockquote class="relative">
              <span class="absolute -top-2 -left-2 text-6xl text-cyan-200 dark:text-cyan-800 font-serif">"</span>
              <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 italic pl-6">Education is what survives when what has been learned has been forgotten.</p>
            </blockquote>
          </section>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Footer -->
      <footer class="mt-16 py-8 border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center space-x-4">
          <img src="/images/logo.png" alt="Logo" class="h-8 w-8" />
          <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">The Other Matthew Miller</span>
          <a href="/sourcesheets" class="text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400 hover:text-cyan-700 dark:hover:text-cyan-300 transition-colors">
            View all source sheets →
          </a>
        </div>
      </footer>
    </div>
  </main>

  <style>
    @font-face {
      font-family: 'Hebrew';
      src: local('Times New Roman'), local('Arial Hebrew'), local('Noto Sans Hebrew');
    }
    
    .font-hebrew {
      font-family: 'Hebrew', serif;
      line-height: 1.8;
    }
  </style>
</Layout>